                              <locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002">Fol. iir(ecto)</locus> Note of ownership: <q>“This Psalter belongs to Ṣägaw, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸጋው፡</foreign>”</q>
                            </desc>
                            </item>

                            <item xml:id="e1">
                              <desc>
                              <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001">Fol. ir(ecto)</locus> Pen trials.</desc>
                              </item>

                            <item xml:id="e2">
                              <locus target="#60v" facs="064">Fol. 60v</locus>
                              <desc>Two marginal symbols surrounded by a line in alternating red and black dots mark the midpoint of the psalms.
                                </desc>
                                </item>

                            <item xml:id="a5">
                              <locus target="#150v" facs="154">Fol. 150v</locus>
                                <desc type="OwnershipNote">Note of ownership: Aläqa Ṭäga, <foreign xml:lang="gez">አለቃ፡ ጠጋ፡</foreign>; and scrawls. </desc>
                                </item>

                            <item xml:id="e3">
                              <desc>
                                Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#35r #64r #131r" facs="038 067 134">folss. 35r, 64r, 131r, </locus>);
                                and lines of text are written interlinearly <locus target="#111r" facs="114">111r, </locus>);
                                and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted <locus target="#30r" facs="033"> f. 30r, line 3</locus>; <locus target="#54v" facs="058"> f. 54v, line 7</locus>);
                                erasure markings are visible <locus target="#30r" facs="033"> f. 30r, line 3</locus>; <locus target="#47v" facs="051"> f. 47v, line 10</locus>; <locus target="#50r" facs="053"> f. 50r, line 3</locus>; <locus target="#52r" facs="055"> f. 52r, line 6</locus>; <locus target="#78v" facs="082"> f. 78v, line 14</locus>; <locus target="#88r" facs="091"> f. 88r, line 8, 14 and 22</locus>; <locus target="#89v" facs="093"> f. 89v, line 14</locus>; etc.);
                                text has been removed <locus target="#53v" facs="057"> f. 53v, line 16</locus>).
                              </desc>
                              </item>
                            <item xml:id="e4">
                              <desc>
                                The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                                appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long,
                                the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line (throughout).
                              </desc>
                              </item>
                        </list>
